Introduction

NewJeans is a five-member girl group under ADOR, a subsidiary label of HYBE.

The group is notable for being formed and developed by Min Hee Jin, who was known to be the former creative director of SM Entertainment and worked closely on the concepts of Red Velvet, f(x), EXO, Girls Generation, and SHINee. Details about NewJeans were kept secret until they made their trailblazing debut on July 22, 2022, by releasing the single "Attention."

On August 1, 2022, NewJeans released their self-titled mini album and went on to earn the nickname 'monster rookies' after topping multiple domestic and international charts.

On July 23, 2024, ADOR revealed that NewJeans would be going on hiatus amidst plagiarism controversy surrounding their song ‘Bubble Gum.’ The agency emphasized the group’s hard work despite setbacks and assured fans that NewJeans would use this break to prepare for exciting projects and return with a fresh look.

On November 28, 2024, NewJeans said in a late-night press conference that they would be departing from their agency, ADOR.
